    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on top-of-the-order efficiency, headlined by **Trea Turner** (81.27) and **Kyle Schwarber** (79.42). Both benefit significantly from a favorable matchup against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez, whose 4.78 xERA provides a soft landing for our elite bats. **Trea Turner** is our strongest play, bolstered by a 10% premium for the leadoff spot and a dynamic platoon advantage. Similarly, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (73.14) and **Hyeseong Kim** (70.16) offer elite upside today; **Pete Crow-Armstrong** thrives on a 14% platoon boost against Kodai Senga, while **Hyeseong Kim** capitalizes on an opportunistic 17% SP skill adjustment. While we are prioritizing stolen base potential, **Yordan Alvarez** (64.91) remains a mandatory start given his high-floor xwOBA, ensuring we maintain a competitive edge in HR and RBI production.\n\nRegarding our roster construction, the most difficult decision involved keeping **Victor Scott II** (47.57) on the bench. While his speed profile is elite, the combination of a lower-tier batting order position (#9) and a neutral matchup against Peter Lambert suppressed his score just enough to keep him behind the more versatile options like **Jerar Encarnacion** and **Carson Benge**. We also continue to monitor **Colt Keith** (47.37), who was close to cracking the utility spot but was ultimately sidelined by a challenging platoon disadvantage against Ranger Suarez. Managers should remain alert: because our current lineup relies on projected batting orders, any late-breaking changes\u2014particularly for **Gary Sanchez** or **Junior Caminero**\u2014could necessitate a pivot to ensure we are maximizing our daily efficiency scores. With **Christian Yelich** still sidelined on the IL, we are relying on our depth to carry the load against several mid-tier arms.",
